During a visit to the LDS Welfare Square in Salt Lake City, President Trump praised the humanitarian efforts of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints (LDS). He commended the church for its work in 180 countries, taking care of people and helping the poor. The President asked the church leaders to share a few words about the care and giving that they do, in the hope that it would inspire others to do the same. The church leaders explained that they provide food and materials to the poor around the world, believing it is their obligation to help those in need. President Trump also mentioned his recent visit to China, where he witnessed the church members bringing supplies for schoolchildren who lacked resources. He expressed his appreciation for the church's efforts and commended Dr. Nelson, a former heart surgeon and leader in the church, for his dedication to helping others. The President thanked everyone and concluded the visit.